==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tether-ball
<hw>Teth"er-ball`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A game played with rackets
and a ball suspended by a string from an upright pole, the object of
each side being to wrap the string around the pole by striking the ball
in a direction opposite to the other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tethydan</ent>⟦br⟧
